cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with image geolocalization, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves retrieval of images from a database, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of deep learning networks for feature extraction and classification suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves kernel density estimation, which is a statistical method, and could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text-based geolocation, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
